.TH "netdev_change_features" 9 "netdev_change_features" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
netdev_change_features \- recalculate device features
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" netdev_change_features
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device to check

Recalculate dev->features set and send notifications even
if they have not changed. Should be called instead of
\fBnetdev_update_features\fP if also dev->vlan_features might
have changed to allow the changes to be propagated to stacked
VLAN devices.
